occurs in association with 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Juniperus occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Idaho and the Oregon high desert. 
<taxonomicName box="[876,1143,1679,1704]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[876,1143,1679,1704]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Juniperus occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also occurs in eastern California and extreme northwestern Nevada where 
<taxonomicName box="[1009,1137,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lithophane" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boogeri">
<emphasis box="[1009,1137,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">L. boogeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is expected to occur.
</paragraph>
